}
```

## Demo
```tsx
import { CinematicHero } from "@/components/ui/cinematic-landing-hero";

export default function CinematicHeroDemo() {
  return (
    <div className="overflow-x-hidden w-[100%] min-h-screen">
      <CinematicHero />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Notes
- Requires GSAP ScrollTrigger plugin. Register it once at module level with `gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)` guarded by `typeof window !== 'undefined'`.
- All CSS is injected via `<style dangerouslySetInnerHTML>` inside the component. Classes like `.premium-depth-card`, `.iphone-bezel`, `.btn-modern-light`, `.btn-modern-dark` are defined there.
- The scroll timeline pins the section for `+=7000` scroll pixels — ensure the page has enough height or the parent layout accommodates this.
- This is a different component from the earlier `animation_cinematic_landing_hero` (animations3_016.md) — this version uses a configurable prop API and includes an iPhone mockup section.
